Citations
Date: 7/11/1833
Source: Early Journals of Henry Williams, The
Author: WILLIAMS
Vol / Page: 341
Edition: 1961
Quote: We walked on to the top of the bank towards the sea about a mile [near Thames], but soon got off the good land, and passed over an entire bed of pudding-stones from 10 to 50 lb. weight. <i>Ibid.</i> 342 The low land did not exceed a quarter of a mile, when we came to rising ground, covered with Kaikatoa - very ordinary.
